# facebook-pro

A starter social app (Next.js + TypeScript + NextAuth + Prisma + Postgres). This scaffold includes authentication (NextAuth with email + Google placeholders) and the ability to create and read posts.

## Requirements

- Node 18+
- npm or yarn
- Docker (for local Postgres) — optional but recommended

## Quickstart (local)

1. Copy the repo files into a folder (facebook-pro).

2. Create a .env file from .env.example and fill values:
   - DATABASE_URL (default points to local Docker Postgres)
   - NEXTAUTH_URL (http://localhost:3000)
   - NEXTAUTH_SECRET (set a strong random value)
   - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID / GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET (optional)
   - EMAIL_SERVER / EMAIL_FROM (for email sign-in)

3. Start local Postgres:
   - docker compose up -d
   - Wait for Postgres to be ready.

4. Install dependencies:
   - npm install

5. Generate Prisma client and run migrations:
   - npx prisma generate
   - npx prisma migrate dev --name init

6. Seed demo users/posts:
   - npx ts-node --transpile-only prisma/seed.ts

7. Run dev server:
   - npm run dev
   - Open http://localhost:3000

## Notes

- NextAuth Email provider requires SMTP credentials (EMAIL_SERVER). Without SMTP, use Google provider after creating OAuth credentials and setting GOOGLE_* env vars.
- To deploy, set env vars in your host (Vercel / Railway / Render) and ensure a managed Postgres is configured.
- Later additions I can implement: image uploads (S3), likes/comments/follow system, real-time notifications, CI.
